Sentencas: The present work concerns studies on synthesis (by chemical co-precipitation) and characterization (microstructural and electrical) of 8 and 10 mol% dysprosia stabilized nanocrystalline cubic-zirconia (DySZ) for use as electrolyte materials in solid oxide fuel cell in the intermediate temperature range.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of nanocrystalline dysprosia stabilized zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Identity and crystallite size of the calcined powders were determined by X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of nanocrystalline dysprosia stabilized zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Microstructural studies of calcined/sintered product by transmission and scanning electron microscopes allowed verification of crystallite/particle size and analysis of morphology/density/distribution of the defects, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of nanocrystalline dysprosia stabilized zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy revealed that the contribution of grain boundary resistance is higher than that of the bulk.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of nanocrystalline dysprosia stabilized zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Furthermore, conductivity analysis evidenced an Arrhenius type thermally activated ionic conduction above 300 degrees C. Thus, DySZ appears a possible alternative to yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) as electrolyte for solid oxide fuel cells due to its lower thermal and comparable ionic conductivity as YSZ.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of nanocrystalline dysprosia stabilized zirconia based electrolyte for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell
